node.title: Kiwi motorbike power couple put love aside to do battle on track
node.description: Avalon Biddle and Jake Lewis will go head-to-head in the New Zealand SuperSport 600 Championship.
node.content: ["As far as sporting power couples go, motorbike riders Avalon Biddle and Jake Lewis will give most a run for their money.", "The pair are famous in the motorsport scene - not only here in New Zealand, but around the world.", "Now, the newly engaged couple are gearing up to go head-to-head to claim the country's top two-wheel crown.", "In 2019, Biddle made history when she became the first woman to win the New Zealand SuperSport 600 Championship.", "To win her second, she'll have to best her other half.", "\"I find it tough on a relationship racing against each other but Jake thinks it's fun, and I try to let that rub off on me and enjoy the experience and try to beat him,\" says Biddle.", "Watch the full story above", "\u00a0"]
